{
  "stem": "20142.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no other way of obtaining any information, except through the people who experience anything like it, or have seen people doing it to the others.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the people we find out that people generally would not try to scare somebody to undertake any such thing, because it was in the interests of the people to survive and survive together with-- with all of them.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, the information about [INAUDIBLE] as finding anybody on a train and throwing him during the running of a train off the train, they were accepted in a way that that's how the new Germany will behave.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I have witnessed the atrocities done to the poor people in Lodz standing in line.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I could very simply tell that this information were quite accurate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When did you get to Warsaw?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We got to Warsaw finally at the beginning of March of 1940.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On a rainy, rainy snow mix day, cold.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "By the way, glad that we reached Warsaw then.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The movement in Warsaw with the-- within within the city was much easier than traveling to Warsaw through the city.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was quite large population and did the same thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If you could-- if you were dressed as-- in civilian clothing, Germans could not tell who was Jew, who was not, unless you would really dress in typical [INAUDIBLE] Jewish garb.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the appearance on their faces are all typical Semitic features.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Give up individual and the Germans started to question them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Especially when it came to the question of IDs and a way of communication.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we came to Warsaw, we had to obtain ID.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's one of the-- the photos of-- that I had on my ID in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had to register with the Jewish community in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
